body: 24 (return) [ Ammianus, in a long, because unseasonable, digression, (xxvi. l, and Valesius, ad locum,) rashly supposes that he understands an astronomical question, of which his readers are ignorant. It is treated with more judgment and propriety by Censorinus (de Die Natali, c. 20) and Macrobius, (Saturnal. i. c. 12-16.) The appellation of _Bissextile_, which marks the inauspicious year, (Augustin. ad Januarium, Epist. 119,) is derived from the _repetition_ of the _sixth_ day of the calends of March.]
